South Korea signed with Japan for a 44.6billion yen credit facility, part of a four billion dlr aidpackage for South Korea's economic development plan to 1988,Foreign Ministry officials here said.    The facility, to be used mostly for building amulti-purpose dam and modernising educational and medicalfacilities and for sewer projects, bears interest of 4.25 pctper year and is repayable over 18 years after a grace period ofseven years. REUTER&#3;